text:
An election was held on November 3, 2020 to elect a Senator from the U.S. state of Nebraska.The four people in the election were Ben Sasse (Republican Party), Chris Janicek (Democratic Party), write-in candidate Preston Love Jr. (Democratic Party), and Gene Siadek (Libertarian Party). Sasse won the election and went back to the Senate for a second term.
This election was strange because Democratic nominee Chris Janicek, lost the support of his party after numerous scandals, write-in candidate Preston Love Jr., got the support of the state Democratic Party instead but Janicek was still on the ballot. There was three primary elections held for the three political parties. The Republican Party primary election was on March 12, 2020. There were two people in the primary election. Ben Sasse won the primary election against Matt Innis. There was seven people in the Democratic Party primary election. Chris Janicek won the primary election. Gene Siadek was the only person in the Libertarian Party primary election. They won the Libertarian Party primary election.
